Integrative medicine: combine evidence-based + complementary. Evidence-based: mindfulness, yoga, tai chi, acupuncture (pain), massage, probiotics specific, omega-3, melatonin sleep, etc. Caution: herbal interactions (St John's Wort, garlic), unregulated. Ask + educate + integrate safely. Multidisciplinary.

ตัวเลือก B (รายละเอียด): Vaccine Immunology + Development + Safety (CDC + ACIP + NIH):

(1) Immune response basics: - Innate: rapid, non-specific (skin, mucosa, complement, phagocytes, NK cells); - Adaptive: specific, memory (T-cell + B-cell); - B-cell → antibodies (IgG, IgM, IgA, IgE); - T-cell → CD4 helper + CD8 cytotoxic; - Memory cells for rapid response on re-exposure;

(2) Vaccine types + how they work: - Live attenuated (MMR, varicella, rotavirus, yellow fever, BCG): weakened pathogen replicates → strong immune response + long duration but contraindicated immunocompromised + pregnancy; - Inactivated whole virus (IPV, hepatitis A, rabies, some flu): killed pathogen safe in immunocompromised; usually need booster; - Subunit / recombinant (HepB, HPV, acellular pertussis, Shingrix, COVID): specific antigens; safe but less immunogenic — adjuvants used; - Toxoid (tetanus, diphtheria): inactivated toxin; - Conjugate (Hib, PCV, meningococcal): protein-conjugated polysaccharide for T-cell-dependent response in young children + better memory; - Polysaccharide (PPSV23): T-cell-independent; less effective < 2 yo; - mRNA (COVID Pfizer + Moderna): lipid nanoparticle delivers mRNA encoding spike protein; novel platform, rapid development, effective + safe in large populations; - Viral vector (J&J COVID, Oxford-AZ COVID, RSV): non-replicating modified virus; - DNA (animal use mostly); - Adjuvants: aluminum, oil-in-water, AS01 (Shingrix), CpG, others — enhance immune response;

(3) Vaccine development pipeline: - Pre-clinical — in vitro + animal models; - Phase 1 — small humans, safety + immunogenicity (~ 100); - Phase 2 — expanded immunogenicity + dose (~ 100-300); - Phase 3 — large efficacy trial (~ 10,000-50,000+); - Approval (FDA BLA, EUA in emergency); - Phase 4 post-marketing surveillance; - Recommendation (ACIP for US); - Traditionally 10-15 yr; COVID vaccines accelerated to ~ 1 yr through parallel processes + emergency funding;

(4) Safety surveillance systems: - VAERS (Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting System) — passive reporting, signal detection; anyone can report; not causation but signal; - VSD (Vaccine Safety Datalink) — large EHR + claims database for safety studies; ~ 12 M people; - CISA (Clinical Immunization Safety Assessment) — expert consultation; - PRISM (Post-Licensure Rapid Immunization Safety Monitoring) — claims-based; - v-safe — COVID smartphone-based; - International: WHO, EMA, others;

(5) Common adverse events: - Local: redness, swelling, soreness — common, mild; - Systemic: fever, headache, fatigue — common, mild, transient (especially mRNA COVID, Shingrix); - Allergic: rare anaphylaxis — observe post-injection; - Serious events: very rare; benefit-risk; - Specific concerns historical: - Wakefield MMR-autism fraud — disproven; - Thimerosal removed pediatric except multi-dose flu (precautionary, no harm shown); - HPV safety reassuring; - COVID mRNA — rare myocarditis (mostly young males, mostly mild self-limited, rate lower than COVID-19 myocarditis); - COVID J&J — rare TTS (thrombosis with thrombocytopenia syndrome) led to limited use; - Rotavirus + intussusception (first version Rotashield withdrawn, current OK); - Oral polio + VAPP (rare paralysis) led to IPV switch in US;

(6) Vaccine injury compensation: - VICP (Vaccine Injury Compensation Program) — no-fault for routine vaccines; - CICP (Countermeasures Injury Compensation Program) — COVID, pandemic countermeasures; - Funded by excise tax on vaccines;

(7) Vaccine hesitancy (see separate);

(8) Future vaccines + technology: - mRNA platform: COVID success accelerating other (flu, RSV, HSV, HIV, malaria, cancer therapeutic vaccines); - Universal flu vaccine; - HIV + TB + malaria — major need; - Cancer vaccines (HPV preventive established; therapeutic emerging); - CMV, RSV, EBV; - Vaccine delivery innovation: needle-free, transdermal, microneedles, oral, thermostable;

(9) Equity in vaccine access + uptake: domestic + global; COVAX international; vaccine equity gaps;

(10) Vaccine communication (see hesitancy);

(11) Multidisciplinary: PCP + nursing + pharmacy + public health + research + manufacturer + regulator + international + community
————————————————
Vaccine science: immune response basics. Types (live, inactivated, subunit, conjugate, mRNA, viral vector). Development phases. Safety surveillance (VAERS, VSD, v-safe). Common AEs vs serious rare. VICP. Hesitancy. Future mRNA + other. Equity. Multidisciplinary.

